The article consists of various statements and releases from federal and state officials, advocacy organizations, businesses, and unions regarding the U.S.-Korea Free Trade Agreement (KORUS). The statements generally express support and satisfaction with the agreement, highlighting its benefits for American exporters, farmers, workers, and manufacturers. They also emphasize the importance of maintaining a strong economic relationship with South Korea and the positive impact of the agreement on bilateral trade, reducing the trade deficit, and expanding export opportunities. Some statements specifically mention the improvements made to the agreement in terms of trade barriers, customs procedures, and access for U.S. industries such as steel, autos, and pharmaceuticals.